channel.title: AryanV2
channel.description:
I've set up a svn server with a free site. I'm hopping to use this to imrove Aryan and make it less detectable.
Available here: http://opensvn.csie.org/AryanV2/
Note: you need to use svn if you want to download it (easily)
Currently it only includes the latest version (377) but i'm want to get some coders and realy improve the code. If you want to contribute, PM me.
Be nice - i'm a n00b to svn. But on the other hand I'm pretty good at coding.
Edit: Getting trac up and running - sry i'm new Edit2: Stick in a one liner about what you gave to the project on startup in bot.java when you contribute Edit3: Post your ideas here (new ticket) https://opensvn.csie.org/traccgi/AryanV2/trac.cgi/wiki
